{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Changing a man's name after marriage.",
        "additional_details": "I believe in equality and for that reason a marriage certificate should be proof enough to change your name even if you are a man taking your wife's name, or a man taking your husband's name. \r\n\r\nLets break the tradition and make a change.",
        "background": "Currently in the UK men are unable to use a marriage certificate as proof to change their name when taking their wife's last name. However woman are allowed to use a marriage certificate as proof to take the mans name. A man has to change his name by deed poll, a woman does not.",
